      "id": "CVE-2026-49414",
      "publishedDate": "2026-06-27T09:22:23.307Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-06-27T09:22:23.307Z",
      "description": "The ELF image activator cleared per-process ASLR preference flags for setuid binaries after the code that computes the PIE base address, rather than before.  As a result, a user-requested ASLR disable was still in effect at the point where the base address was chosen.\n\nAn unprivileged local user can disable ASLR for a setuid PIE binary by calling procctl(2) before execve(2).  This makes exploitation of any separate memory corruption vulnerability in that binary significantly easier.",
      "severity": "N/A",
      "references": [
